<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id56daba40-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s4104"><num value="4104">§ 4104.</num><heading> Availability of facilities and appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The services and facilities of and appropriations for the Coast Guard shall be available to effectuate the purposes of the Reserve and the Auxiliary.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id56daba41-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">(<ref href="/us/act/1949-08-04/ch393">Aug. 4, 1949, ch. 393</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/63/557">63 Stat. 557</ref>, § 894; renumbered § 4104, <ref href="/us/pl/115/282/tI/s120/b">Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 120(b)</ref>, <date date="2018-12-04">Dec. 4, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4237">132 Stat. 4237</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id56daba42-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id56daba43-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 14, U.S.C., 1946 ed., § 354 (<ref href="/us/act/1941-02-19/ch8">Feb. 19, 1941, ch. 8</ref>, title III, § 304, <ref href="/us/stat/55/14">55 Stat. 14</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Changes were made in phraseology. 81st Congress, House Report No. 557.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id56daba44-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
